metadata.name: Hotline #58
metadata.description:
--CONTROLS--

[S]: Save PNG
[Z]: Zoom
[F]: Fullscreen
[L]: Light

------------

Focus, dedication
Allowing yourself to be

Break the pattern to see what is left,
when you have nothing to hold on to.

This is about making choices
Removing the noise
Looking inwards
Transcendence

The only real hotline you have
is the connection with yourself

------------

released under CC BY-NC 4.0.

Tijn Arts, 2022

metadata.name: Nounfall #107
metadata.description:
Nounfall is drawn exclusively from the 234 heads and 21 glasses that are used to build the current Nouns collection. The background colors are all pulled from the blessed Noun palette.

This is ok because Nouns are CC0, which basically means public domain. Check out nouns.wtf for more info.

They make for fun social media banners when cropped, if you wanna show off you fandom of Nouns.

C : Clear screen and start animation over
S : Save current image
1 -> 6 : Set pixel density to the respective number

So, if you want a high resolution file, tap `6` for it to redraw, and then `S` to save. You can also save while it's animating if you like, which is fun too.

metadata.name: Plottable Thousands #77
metadata.description:
'Thousands' explores the packing of recursive circles and golden angle spirals distributing various particles on a A4 canvas.

A SVG file can be exported (right click save) to plot the piece physically.

You can enjoy the digital version that simulate ink effects and optional, thanks to the utility token decoupling, get a physical one: the digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art piece, owning it confers the right to plot or request a physical plot from @greweb (https://greweb.me/plots/nft). @greweb would use fountain pens but other plotting artists are free to achieve it with their own materials and ship to collectors â€“ as long as NFT is owned at request time.

Code: https://github.com/gre/gre/tree/master/doodles/plottable-thousands

@greweb â€“ 2022 â€“ tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM â€“ CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

metadata.name: BBL #31
metadata.description:
BBL tries to recreate the wonderful feeling when colors mix and blend together and spark something entirely new and exciting. It represents the wonderful space that I found comfort and freedom in with generative art. 

You can press 's' to save a hi-res (1600px x 1600px) image of the generated artwork.
